    Model Tenancy Clauses (Northern Ireland)
  </h1>

  <p style="text-align: center; font-size: 10pt; color: #666; margin: 20px 0;">
    Northern Ireland | Private Tenancy Agreement | Private Tenancies Act (Northern Ireland) 2022
  </p>

  <div style="background-color: #fff3cd; border-left: 4px solid #ffc107; padding: 15px; margin: 30px 0;">
    <p style="margin: 0; font-weight: bold;">Important Notice</p>
    <p style="margin: 10px 0 0 0;">
      These are the model tenancy clauses for Private Tenancy Agreements under the Private Tenancies
      Act (Northern Ireland) 2022. Your tenancy agreement incorporates these clauses as required by
      Northern Ireland law. This appendix provides the full text for reference.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>1. Rent</h2>
  <p>
    The Tenant agrees to pay the Rent on the days and in the manner specified in this Agreement.
  </p>
  <p>
    Rent is payable in advance. The Landlord may only increase the rent by following the statutory
    procedure set out in the Private Tenancies Act (Northern Ireland) 2022. This requires giving
    the tenant at least one month's notice in writing before the increase takes effect.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Deposit Protection</h2>
  <p>
    If the Landlord takes a deposit, they must protect it in an approved tenancy deposit scheme within
    14 days of receiving it. The Landlord must provide prescribed information about the deposit protection
    to the Tenant within 28 days of receiving the deposit.
  </p>
