  <h2>3. Tenancy Deposit Information</h2>
  <p>
    The Landlord must provide the Tenant with the following information about the deposit:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>The name and contact details of the deposit scheme</li>
    <li>The amount of the deposit protected</li>
    <li>How to apply for the release of the deposit at the end of the tenancy</li>
    <li>Information about the dispute resolution service</li>
    <li>The circumstances in which the landlord may retain all or part of the deposit</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Condition of Property - Fitness for Habitation</h2>
  <p>
    The Landlord must ensure the property is fit for human habitation. This includes ensuring:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>The property is free from serious damp</li>
    <li>The property has adequate heating and ventilation</li>
    <li>The property has natural and artificial lighting</li>
    <li>The property has an adequate and wholesome water supply</li>
    <li>The property has satisfactory facilities for the preparation of food</li>
    <li>The property has a suitably located toilet for exclusive use</li>
    <li>The property is in a reasonable state of repair</li>
    <li>The property is structurally stable</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Landlord's Repair Obligations</h2>
  <p>
    The Landlord must:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Keep in repair the structure and exterior (including drains, gutters, external pipes)</li>
    <li>Keep in repair and working order the installations for water, gas, electricity, heating, and hot water</li>
    <li>Keep in repair and working order sanitary installations (baths, sinks, toilets)</li>
    <li>Provide a valid Gas Safety Certificate annually (if the property has gas)</li>
    <li>Carry out an electrical safety inspection every 5 years</li>
    <li>Fit smoke alarms on every storey and carbon monoxide alarms where required</li>
    <li>Provide an Energy Performance Certificate (EPC)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. Tenant's Obligations</h2>
  <p>
    The Tenant agrees to:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Keep the property clean and in good condition</li>
    <li>Promptly report any defects or disrepair to the Landlord</li>
    <li>Not damage or alter the property without written consent</li>
    <li>Not use the property for any illegal purpose</li>
    <li>Return the property in the same condition at the end of the tenancy (fair wear and tear excepted)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>7. Access for Repairs</h2>
  <p>
    The Tenant must allow the Landlord reasonable access to inspect the property and carry out repairs,
    subject to giving at least 24 hours' written notice (except in emergencies).
  </p>

  <h2>8. Subletting and Assignment</h2>
  <p>
    The Tenant must not:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Sublet the whole or part of the property</li>
    <li>Assign or transfer the tenancy</li>
    <li>Take in lodgers</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Without the Landlord's prior written consent.</p>

  <h2>9. Notice to End Tenancy</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Tenant's Notice:</strong> The Tenant may end a periodic tenancy by giving the Landlord at
    least 4 weeks' written notice (or such longer period as specified in the tenancy agreement).
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Landlord's Notice:</strong> The Landlord may end a periodic tenancy by serving a Notice to Quit
    giving at least:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>4 weeks:</strong> If the tenancy is less than 12 months old</li>
    <li><strong>8 weeks:</strong> If the tenancy is more than 12 months old</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    For fixed-term tenancies, notice requirements depend on the terms of the agreement and whether
    any ground for possession applies.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Tenant's Right to Quiet Enjoyment</h2>
  <p>
    The Tenant has the right to "quiet enjoyment" of the property. The Landlord must not interfere with
    the Tenant's use and enjoyment of the property without lawful excuse.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Landlord Registration</h2>
  <p>
    Landlords in certain areas of Northern Ireland are required to register with the local council.
    The Landlord Registration Scheme aims to improve standards in the private rented sector.
    You can check landlord registration at <a href="https://www.nidirect.gov.uk">www.nidirect.gov.uk</a>.
  </p>

